173
00:11:51,908 --> 00:11:53,303
No.

174
00:11:53,405 --> 00:11:55,503
- Well, then, for what?
- I don't know. With my friends.

175
00:11:55,608 --> 00:11:57,202
In case we stop for pizza or something.

176
00:11:57,306 --> 00:11:59,701
Are there children at this
midnight circle, because if not,

177
00:11:59,805 --> 00:12:03,402
please, take me there now.

178
00:12:04,807 --> 00:12:08,701
Hey, do you know what it is, Ned?
The midnight circle?

179
00:12:08,806 --> 00:12:10,900
Um, no.

180
00:12:11,008 --> 00:12:14,101
Never heard of it.

181
00:12:21,505 --> 00:12:24,803
So, Jim is working tonight,

182
00:12:24,908 --> 00:12:28,103
and I am starving. You want to go
to Lento's and grab a bite?

183
00:12:28,205 --> 00:12:31,301
Oh, I would love to, but I really
have to make sure that Ned's

184
00:12:31,407 --> 00:12:33,102
doing his homework.
Can I get a raincheck?

185
00:12:33,207 --> 00:12:38,100
- Yeah, no problem. Good night.
- Ok. Good night.

186
00:13:20,007 --> 00:13:23,003
You don't belong.

187
00:13:30,908 --> 00:13:32,503
They were just giving me a ride home.

188
00:13:32,606 --> 00:13:34,403
I don't want you in a car
with people I don't know.

189
00:13:34,508 --> 00:13:38,101
- Those kids are too old for you, Ned.
- They like me. They're my friends.

190
00:13:38,205 --> 00:13:40,802
- Wait. That's your study group?
- What's the big deal?

191
00:13:40,905 --> 00:13:42,402
The big deal is I'm your mother. 

192
00:13:42,508 --> 00:13:44,602
I want to know who you're with
and where you are.

193
00:13:44,707 --> 00:13:48,702
- You want to control everything I do.
- Most of it, yes. That's my job.

194
00:13:48,808 --> 00:13:53,602
You are not an adult yet, Ned,
as much as you think you are.

195
00:13:53,706 --> 00:13:56,600
And don't blame Melinda. She told me
because she cares about you,

196
00:13:56,705 --> 00:13:59,501
not because she wanted to
get you in trouble.

197
00:13:59,606 --> 00:14:03,102
I could tell things, too.

198
00:14:08,308 --> 00:14:13,102
- Hey, where are you going?
- Home, to prison.

199
00:14:13,907 --> 00:14:15,602
Ned!

200
00:14:15,706 --> 00:14:17,103
I  keep your secrets.

201
00:14:17,207 --> 00:14:19,703
Hey, that's not what this is about.

202
00:14:19,805 --> 00:14:21,103
Who were those guys?

203
00:14:21,208 --> 00:14:23,403
They go to my school.
They help me study.

204
00:14:23,607 --> 00:14:25,601
Now I look totally lame.

205
00:14:25,706 --> 00:14:29,000
Look, there was a bumper sticker with
numbers on it. What does it mean?

206
00:14:29,108 --> 00:14:31,102
Hey.

207
00:14:31,207 --> 00:14:33,101
I know when I talked about
the midnight circle yesterday

208
00:14:33,205 --> 00:14:34,800
- that you knew what it was.
- I don't.

209
00:14:34,907 --> 00:14:37,103
I'm not playing around, Ned.

210
00:14:37,206 --> 00:14:38,903
There is a ghost attached
to your friends,

211
00:14:39,008 --> 00:14:41,503
or the midnight circle,
whatever it is.

212
00:14:41,605 --> 00:14:44,200
A dangerous ghost.
You have to tell me.

213
00:14:44,305 --> 00:14:47,600
I don't know anything.

214
00:15:01,105 --> 00:15:03,603
- Hi. I'm...
- Melinda Gordon. Yes.

215
00:15:03,707 --> 00:15:05,600
I know all about you.

216
00:15:05,707 --> 00:15:08,201
I'm Kate Payne.

217
00:15:08,306 --> 00:15:10,900
